Artemis-Moon Goddess <br>
Artemis is one of the principle Goddesses of Greek mythology.   She was the daughter of the God Zeus and Leto.   She was chief  hunter to the Gods and Goddesses. <br>
<br>
Goddess of hunting and wild animals especially bears. <br>
Artemis was also the Goddess of childbirth, of nature, and of the harvest.   As the Moon Goddess, she was sometimes identified with the Goddess Selene and Hectate. <br>
